\layout Standard

This result is significant because it is not possible for 
\begin_inset Formula $4-$
\end_inset 

point subdivision schemes to reproduce polynomials of degree 4.
 Even if we include non-interpolatory subdivision schemes, for a given 
\begin_inset Formula $k\in \Z $
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{j+1,2k+1}$
\end_inset 

 cannot be computed solely from the neighbouring values 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{j,k-1}$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{j,k}$
\end_inset 

,
\begin_inset Formula $y_{j,k+1}$
\end_inset 

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{j,k+1}$
\end_inset 

